The Marine’s family, who live in a detached former farmhouse in Royston, near Barnsley, South Yorkshire, were devastated at being told of his death on Monday.

In a statement, they said: ‘His flame might have burned briefly but it burned brightly with love, courage, conviction and honour and we are very proud of him.’

Last night video footage emerged of the Afghanistan veteran in Syria wearing combat gear, jeans and a black T-shirt.

Speaking to the camera he says: ‘My name is Konstandinos Erik Scurfield. I came here on my own free will and I came here to help.’

It also emerged that he was questioned by police last October on suspicion of going to Syria to fight jihadists. 

